{"title": "Shortstop", "description": "Zane Grey (Pearl Zane Gray) born in 1872 in Zanesville, Ohio was best known for his western stories, most notably <i>Riders Of The Purple Sage</i> which has been filmed four times, the last in 1996 starring Ed Harris and Amy Madigan. Among his other interests was baseball. He attended the University of Pennsylvania on a baseball scholarship where he earned a degree in dentistry. Grey later played minor league baseball with a team in Wheeling, West Virginia. According to the Internet Movie Data Base he is credited with 110 films made from his stories and books. Grey died from a heart attack in 1939 in Altadena, California.<br></br>In The Shortstop (1909) drawing on his baseball experience Grey follows the adventures of seventeen year-old Chase Alloway on his quest to make his fortune as a baseball player and lift his family out of poverty. Along the way young Chase encounters hardship and set-back. But with perseverance he discovers not only himself but friendship and love.  (summary by Rowdy Delaney)", "duration": 19001, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "965", "name": "Zane Grey"}], "coverArt": "https://www.archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt4/Shortstop_the_1004.jpg", "copyright_year": "1909", "genres": ["Sports Fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Rowdy Delaney"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Rowdy Delaney"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "J. M. Smallheer"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Persuading Mother", "readers": [1867], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/shortshop_rd_librivox/shortstop_01_grey_64kb.mp3", "duration": 521}, {"section": 2, "title": "Riding Away", "readers": [1867], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/shortshop_rd_librivox/shortstop_02_grey_64kb.mp3", "duration": 448}, {"section": 3, "title": "Fame", "readers": [1867], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/shortshop_rd_librivox/shortstop_03_grey_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1219}, {"section":